Use FINEMAPR to use FINEMAP, Caviar, and Paintor

Questions: Zscore vs. Pvalue in eQTLGen data

FINEMAP

http://www.christianbenner.com/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4495769/

Instructions: https://variani.github.io/finemapr/vignettes/finemapr.html

If using straight FINEMAP, need to include inputs: Master file Z file - minor allele frequencies, beta, and se in z-file LD file BGEN, BGI, SAMPLE, and INCL file

https://github.com/topics/finemap https://github.com/variani/finemapr and https://variani.github.io/finemapr/vignettes/finemapr.html https://github.com/slwest/finemap-scripts

Google search: FINEMAP https://github.com/Ensembl/Finemap https://github.com/jinghuazhao/FM-pipeline https://github.com/manning-lab/fineMap https://github.com/chr1swallace/finemap-psa https://github.com/opentargets/genetics-finemapping https://omictools.com/finemap-tool https://github.com/JoniColeman/gwas_scripts/blob/master/README.md

1000 Genomes https://www.google.com/search?q=background+finemap&oq=background+finemap&aqs=chrome..69i57.1595j0j1&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8 https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/FINEMAP%3A-efficient-variable-selection-using-summary-Benner-Spencer/08f23c6b03aa51eb83948b750162b63810f838cc https://www.google.com/search?q=1000+genomes+plink+files&oq=1000+genomes+&aqs=chrome.4.69i57j0l5.4991j0j1&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8 https://www.google.com/search?q=1000+genomes+background+score+regression&oq=1000+genomes+background+score+regression&aqs=chrome..69i57.3654j0j1&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8 http://www.internationalgenome.org/data/

git clone https://github.com/gkichaev/PAINTOR_V3.0 git clone https://github.com/fhormoz/caviar git clone https://github.com/variani/finemapr

http://genetics.cs.ucla.edu/caviar/caviar_manual.pdf http://zarlab.cs.ucla.edu/tag/ecaviar/
